  <main class="content-left">
    <h1>Spark to Flame</h1>

    <p><strong>Spark to Flame</strong> is a guide to capturing those deep, high-energy feelings that come from being "seen" or admired—and learning to recreate them from within.</p>

    <h2 class="gold-underline">Core Mantras</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>“This feeling is me, not them.”</strong> – The spark lives in you; they only reminded you.</li>
      <li><strong>“Nothing shakes me—I stand in my own axis.”</strong> – A quick reset that cuts through fog.</li>
      <li><strong>“I savor the spark, but I am the flame.”</strong> – Keep the energy but own the source.</li>
      <li><strong>“People come, people go—their absence is freedom, not loss.”</strong></li>
      <li><strong>“I am the pillar; the wind passes, but I do not move.”</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="gold-underline">How to Capture the Feelings</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Pause:</strong> When the spark happens, freeze the moment. Feel it fully.</li>
      <li><strong>Anchor:</strong> Put a hand on your chest or form a small circle with your fingers. Link the feeling to a deep breath.</li>
      <li><strong>Replay:</strong> Later, recall it like a movie. Pause at the peak moment and breathe it into your chest.</li>
      <li><strong>Recreate:</strong> Use music, posture, or the image of being "seen" to bring the state back on demand.</li>
      <li><strong>Extract:</strong> Ask: “What quality in them awakened me?” Then practice building that in yourself.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="gold-underline">The Shift</h2>
    <p>The spark was never about them. They were just the match. <strong>You are the flame.</strong></p>
